{
  "cells": [
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "---\n",
        "title: \"Convolutional Neural Networks (CNN)\"\n",
        "author: \"Miguel Fonseca\"\n",
        "format:\n",
        "  revealjs:\n",
        "    toc: true\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "# Motivation\n",
        "\n",
        "## Why not Fully Connected Networks for Images?\n",
        "\n",
        "- Images: 224×224×3 → 150,528 features\n",
        "- Dense layer with 1,000 neurons:\n",
        "  \n",
        "$$\n",
        "150,528 \\times 1000 = 150M \\text{ parameters}\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "Problems:\n",
        "\n",
        "- Too many parameters\n",
        "- No spatial structure\n",
        "- No translation invariance\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "## Key Ideas Behind CNNs\n",
        "\n",
        "::: {.incremental}\n",
        "1. **Local connectivity**\n",
        "    \n",
        "    Earliest layers of the network focus on local regions.\n",
        "\n",
        "3. **Translation equivariance**\n",
        "    \n",
        "    The network should respond similarly to the same patch, regardless of where it appears in the image (*translation invariance*).\n",
        "4. **Hierarchical feature learning**\n",
        "    Deeper layers should be able to capture longer-range features of the image\n",
        ":::\n",
        "\n",
        "# Convolutions\n",
        "\n",
        "## Continuous Convolution\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "(f * g)(t) = \\int_{-\\infty}^{\\infty} f(\\tau) g(t - \\tau) d\\tau\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "Interpretation:\n",
        "\n",
        "- Flip one function\n",
        "- Slide it\n",
        "- Compute overlap (inner product)\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "![](/images/continuous_convolution_anim.gif)\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "## Discrete Convolution (1D)\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "(y * k)[n] = \\sum_{m=-\\infty}^{\\infty} y[m] \\cdot k[n - m]\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "In practice (finite signals):\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "z[i] = \\sum_{j=0}^{K-1} x[i-j] \\cdot w[j]\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "![](/images/discrete_convolution_anim.gif)\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "## Convolution as Sliding Dot Product\n",
        "\n",
        "- Kernel (filter) = small learnable weight matrix\n",
        "    - Slide across input\n",
        "    - Compute dot product\n",
        "\n",
        "This is:\n",
        "\n",
        "- A linear operator\n",
        "- With shared weights\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "## Convolution vs Cross-Correlation\n",
        "\n",
        "Deep learning frameworks usually compute:\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "z[i] = \\sum_{j=0}^{K-1} x[i+j] w[j]\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "(No flipping.)\n",
        "\n",
        "# 1D Convolutions\n",
        "\n",
        "## When do we use them?\n",
        "\n",
        "- Time series\n",
        "- Audio\n",
        "- Financial data\n",
        "- Genomics sequences\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "## 1D Convolution Example\n",
        "\n",
        "Input:\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "x = [1, 2, 3, 4, 5]\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "Kernel:\n",
        "$$\n",
        "w = [1, 0, -1]\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "Output (stride 1):\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "z[0] = 1*1 + 2*0 + 3*(-1)\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "## 1D Convolution in TensorFlow"
      ],
      "id": "933014f2"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "import tensorflow as tf\n",
        "\n",
        "model = tf.keras.Sequential([\n",
        "    tf.keras.layers.Conv1D(\n",
        "        filters=32,\n",
        "        kernel_size=3,\n",
        "        activation='relu',\n",
        "        input_shape=(100, 1)\n",
        "    )\n",
        "])"
      ],
      "id": "ea2a91cd",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "![](/images/1d_convolution.png)\n",
        "\n",
        "# 2D Convolutions\n",
        "\n",
        "## 2D Convolutions\n",
        "\n",
        "Used for:\n",
        "\n",
        "- Images\n",
        "- Video frames\n",
        "- Spatial data\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "## 2D Convolution Formula\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "Z(i,j) = \\sum_m \\sum_n X(i+m, j+n) W(m,n)\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "Kernel is now a matrix.\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "## Convolution Over RGB Images\n",
        "\n",
        "Input shape:\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "H \\times W \\times C\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "Kernel shape:\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "k \\times k \\times C\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "Each filter spans all channels.\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "![](/images/2d_convolution_anim.gif)\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "## Multiple Filters\n",
        "\n",
        "**If we use 64 filters:**\n",
        "\n",
        "Output depth:\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "H' \\times W' \\times 64\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "Each filter learns a feature:\n",
        "\n",
        "- edges\n",
        "- textures\n",
        "- shapes\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "## 2D Convolution in TensorFlow"
      ],
      "id": "58f777fc"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "model = tf.keras.Sequential([\n",
        "    tf.keras.layers.Conv2D(\n",
        "        filters=32,\n",
        "        kernel_size=(3,3),\n",
        "        activation='relu',\n",
        "        input_shape=(28, 28, 1)\n",
        "    )\n",
        "])"
      ],
      "id": "f30907bf",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "# Padding\n",
        "\n",
        "## Why padding?\n",
        "\n",
        "Without padding:\n",
        "\n",
        "- Spatial dimensions shrink\n",
        "\n",
        "With kernel size 3:\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "$$H_{out} = h - 2$$\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "## Types of Padding\n",
        "\n",
        "### Valid Padding\n",
        "\n",
        "- No padding\n",
        "- Output shrinks\n",
        "\n",
        "### Same Padding\n",
        "\n",
        "- Zero-padding\n",
        "- Output size preserved\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "## Output Size Formula\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "H_{out} = \\frac{H + 2P - K}{S} + 1\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "Where:\n",
        "\n",
        "- $P$: padding\n",
        "- $K$: kernel size\n",
        "- $S$: stride\n",
        "\n",
        "# Pooling\n",
        "\n",
        "## Why Pooling?\n",
        "\n",
        "::: {.incremental}\n",
        "- Downsample feature maps\n",
        "- Reduce parameters\n",
        "- Increase receptive field\n",
        "- Add translation invariance\n",
        ":::\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "## Types of Pooling\n",
        "\n",
        "### Max Pooling\n",
        "\n",
        "$$Z = \\max(x_{window})$$\n",
        "\n",
        "Keeps strongest activation.\n",
        "\n",
        "### Average Pooling\n",
        "\n",
        "$$Z = \\text{mean}(x_{window})$$\n",
        "\n",
        "Smoother representation.\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "## Pooling in TensorFlow"
      ],
      "id": "e441f92b"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "tf.keras.layers.MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2,2))"
      ],
      "id": "6bc95454",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "# CNN Architecture\n",
        "\n",
        "## CNN Architecture Pattern\n",
        "\n",
        "Typical CNN:\n",
        "\n",
        "Conv → ReLU → Conv → ReLU → Pool\n",
        "\n",
        "Conv → ReLU → Conv → ReLU → Pool\n",
        "\n",
        "Flatten → Dense → Output\n",
        "\n",
        "### Example CNN (MNIST)"
      ],
      "id": "2ab6a28c"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "model = tf.keras.Sequential([\n",
        "    tf.keras.layers.Conv2D(32, 3, activation='relu', padding='same'),\n",
        "    tf.keras.layers.MaxPooling2D(2),\n",
        "    tf.keras.layers.Conv2D(64, 3, activation='relu', padding='same'),\n",
        "    tf.keras.layers.MaxPooling2D(2),\n",
        "    tf.keras.layers.Flatten(),\n",
        "    tf.keras.layers.Dense(128, activation='relu'),\n",
        "    tf.keras.layers.Dense(10, activation='softmax')\n",
        "])"
      ],
      "id": "32b62278",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "## Receptive Field\n",
        "\n",
        "The receptive field grows with depth.\n",
        "\n",
        "**Deeper neurons:**\n",
        "\n",
        "- \"see\" larger parts of image\n",
        "- learn abstract features\n",
        "\n",
        "# Residual Networks\n",
        "\n",
        "## Vanishing Gradient Problem\n",
        "\n",
        "Deep CNNs suffer from:\n",
        "\n",
        "- Gradient decay\n",
        "- Hard optimization\n",
        "- Solution: Residual Connections\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "## Residual Connections\n",
        "\n",
        "Introduced in:\n",
        "\n",
        ">ResNet (2015) [REF AQUI]\n",
        "\n",
        "Instead of learning:\n",
        "\n",
        "$$HD(x)$$\n",
        "\n",
        "Learn:\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "F(x) = H(x) - x\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "So:\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "H(x) = F(x) + x\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "## Residual Block\n",
        "\n",
        "Output:\n",
        "\n",
        "$$y = F(x) + x$$\n",
        "\n",
        "This is called a **skip connection**.\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "## Why Residuals Help\n",
        "\n",
        "- Easier optimization\n",
        "- Identity mapping available\n",
        "- Prevents degradation\n",
        "- Enables 100+ layer networks\n",
        "\n",
        "## Residual Block in TensorFlow"
      ],
      "id": "7e568921"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "from tensorflow.keras import layers\n",
        "\n",
        "def residual_block(x, filters):\n",
        "    shortcut = x\n",
        "    \n",
        "    x = layers.Conv2D(filters, 3, padding='same', activation='relu')(x)\n",
        "    x = layers.Conv2D(filters, 3, padding='same')(x)\n",
        "    \n",
        "    x = layers.Add()([x, shortcut])\n",
        "    x = layers.Activation('relu')(x)\n",
        "    \n",
        "    return x"
      ],
      "id": "9c7f7ad5",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "## Full CNN with Residuals"
      ],
      "id": "6847cb19"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "inputs = tf.keras.Input(shape=(32,32,3))\n",
        "x = tf.keras.layers.Conv2D(32, 3, padding='same')(inputs)\n",
        "\n",
        "x = residual_block(x, 32)\n",
        "x = tf.keras.layers.MaxPooling2D()(x)\n",
        "\n",
        "x = residual_block(x, 32)\n",
        "x = tf.keras.layers.GlobalAveragePooling2D()(x)\n",
        "\n",
        "outputs = tf.keras.layers.Dense(10, activation='softmax')(x)\n",
        "\n",
        "model = tf.keras.Model(inputs, outputs)"
      ],
      "id": "af42eab8",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    }
  ],
